focus_view_model.news_headline: Willdan stock slides after FY2026 outlook flags softness
focus_view_model.news_summary: Post-results narrative shifted to forward-year uncertainty, triggering a high-conviction re-pricing despite a headline beat.

logic_pillars.technical: F3 DOWNTREND; F1 89.14 (Close, 2026-02-27) below F2 SMA200=94.27 and far below F4 EMA55=114.21 / F5 EMA21=114.96; regime M5=RISK_OFF amplifies downside skew.
logic_pillars.volume_analysis: V1 RVOL20=3.68 confirms institutional distribution; this is not a low-liquidity air pocket—flow is decisive.
logic_pillars.news_catalyst: N1=unavailable; see external_intel: forward outlook/guidance framing dominated the reaction.

focus_view_model.divergence: F6 SA Overall=Buy failing vs F3 downtrend: the market is discounting forward-year trajectory; V1 spike suggests institutions are exiting/derisking rather than debating valuation.
focus_view_model.action_plan: Risk-off (M5): avoid dip-buying until trend repair. First technical reclaim is F2 SMA200=94.27; meaningful repair requires reclaim of F4 EMA55=114.21 (and ideally F5 EMA21=114.96).

logic_pillars.volume_analysis: V1 RVOL20=1.02 suggests positioning is not yet crowded; the move risk is catalyst-driven rather than flow-driven.
logic_pillars.news_catalyst: N1=unavailable; see external_intel: earnings call timing + prior preannouncement makes this a binary tape-read setup.

focus_view_model.divergence: F6 SA Overall=Strong Buy conflicts with F3 downtrend; market is demanding confirmation from the upcoming event before re-rating can translate into price.
focus_view_model.action_plan: Treat as event-risk trade: no “trend” entry until post-event reclaim of F5 EMA21=123.56; higher-confidence repair requires reclaim of F2 SMA200=125.82 and then F4 EMA55=132.77.
